726089f-a.title: Queens: Astoria Boulevard - 75th Street
726089f-a.text:
Astoria Boulevard, at the S.W. corner of 75th Street,
showing Mrs. Blackwell's house of 1873. It stood just east
of St. Michaels Cemetery. The property was owned by J. L.
Riker in 1909. Astoria Boulevard, here, is the former
Flushing Avenue.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection  April, 1923
